# FHEVM v0.11 - Windsurf rules

Active when the workspace touches `@fhevm/solidity`, `@fhevm/hardhat-plugin`,
`@fhevm/mock-utils`, `@zama-fhe/relayer-sdk` (legacy primitives),
`@zama-fhe/sdk` (new high-level SDK v3+), `@zama-fhe/react-sdk` (new React
hooks v3+), or `@openzeppelin/confidential-contracts`; declares
`euint*` / `ebool` / `eaddress` / `externalEuint*`; inherits
`ZamaEthereumConfig`; uses `ZamaSDK`, `Token`, `ReadonlyToken`,
`RelayerWeb`, `RelayerNode`, `RelayerCleartext`, `ViemSigner`,
`EthersSigner`, `WagmiSigner`, `WrappersRegistry`, `indexedDBStorage`,
`chromeSessionStorage`, or any of the 59 React hooks (`useShield`,
`useUnshield`, `useConfidentialBalance`, `useConfidentialTransfer`,
`useAllow`, `useUserDecrypt`, `useDelegateDecryption`, `useActivityFeed`,
etc.); or hits any FHEVM custom error (`SenderNotAllowed`, `ACLNotAllowed`,
`InvalidKMSSignatures`, `KMSInvalidSigner`, `EmptyDecryptionProof`,
`DivisionByZero`, `NotPowerOfTwo`, `HCUTransactionLimitExceeded`,
`HCUTransactionDepthLimitExceeded`) or new-SDK error
(`SigningRejectedError`, `NoCiphertextError`,
`InsufficientConfidentialBalanceError`, `InsufficientERC20BalanceError`,
`BalanceCheckUnavailableError`, `KeypairExpiredError`,
`RelayerRequestFailedError`, `DelegationNotPropagatedError`,
`DelegationCooldownError`).

If none of the above applies, ignore this file.

## What FHEVM is

Contracts operate on opaque `bytes32` handles, not on ciphertexts. A coprocessor
performs FHE math off-chain. `ebool` is a `bytes32` UDVT, so:

- `if (ebool)` and `require(ebool)` are Solidity compile errors.
- The trap is unwrapping (`ebool.unwrap(r) != bytes32(0)`); the handle is always
  non-zero, so the check always passes. Use `FHE.select` for any branch on an
  encrypted value.

Every encrypted handle has an ACL. Missing `FHE.allowThis` loses the handle
next transaction. Missing `FHE.allow(value, user)` makes user decryption
revert with `SenderNotAllowed`.

## Required setup

```solidity
pragma solidity ^0.8.28;
import { FHE, euint64, externalEuint64, ebool } from "@fhevm/solidity/lib/FHE.sol";
import { ZamaEthereumConfig } from "@fhevm/solidity/config/ZamaConfig.sol";
contract MyContract is ZamaEthereumConfig { }
```

Pragma: `^0.8.28` (default). `^0.8.27` minimum when importing
`@openzeppelin/confidential-contracts`. EVM target: `cancun`.

## ALWAYS

- Call `FHE.allowThis(value)` after every stored encrypted computation.
- Call `FHE.allow(value, user)` for every value a user must decrypt.
- Use `FHE.fromExternal(externalVal, inputProof)` for user-submitted inputs;
  `FHE.asEuintXX(literal)` is plaintext-to-encrypted only.
- Use `FHE.select` for branching on `ebool`; never `if` / `require` / `assert`.
- Verify every function name, address, and import path against installed
  source under `node_modules/@fhevm/solidity/` and
  `node_modules/@zama-fhe/relayer-sdk/`. Source > skill references > Zama
  docs > training knowledge. On conflict, source wins.

## ASK FIRST (do not decide unilaterally)

- Public vs user decryption (visibility model differs).
- Encrypted bit width above `euint64` (HCU and gas cost rise sharply).
- Replay protection on finalization functions.
- ERC-7984 vs custom confidential ERC-20.

## NEVER

- `TFHE.*` - the library is `FHE`. `TFHE` does not compile.
- `SepoliaConfig` as a Solidity base - removed in v0.9. Use
  `ZamaEthereumConfig`. (The `SepoliaConfig` exported by
  `@zama-fhe/relayer-sdk/web` is unrelated and still correct.)
- `FHE.requestDecryption`, `GatewayCaller`, `FHE.verifySignatures` - removed
  or renamed in v0.9. Public decryption is `makePubliclyDecryptable` ->
  off-chain `publicDecrypt` -> on-chain `checkSignatures`.
- `FHE.allowForDecryption(handle)` as a library helper - never existed.
  Use `FHE.makePubliclyDecryptable(handle)`.
- `FHE.neq` / `FHE.lte` / `FHE.gte` - use `FHE.ne` / `FHE.le` / `FHE.ge`.
- `fhevmjs`, `@fhevm/sdk`, `@zama-ai/fhevm`, bare `fhevm` - deprecated or
  never existed. Use `@zama-fhe/relayer-sdk` with `/web`, `/bundle`, or
  `/node` sub-path.
- Bare relayer-sdk import (`from '@zama-fhe/relayer-sdk'`) - subpath required.
- `initFhevm()` - the function is `initSDK()` (browser only).
- `results.values[handle]` - the field is `results.clearValues[handle]`.
- `view` / `pure` on a function that calls FHE math, ACL grants,
  `fromExternal`, `makePubliclyDecryptable`, `checkSignatures`, or
  `randEuintX`. Those write coprocessor state and revert in `view`/`pure`.
- Encrypted loop bound (`for (uint i = 0; i < euint64Val; i++)`) - compile
  error. Fix the iteration count plaintext, gate work with `FHE.select`.
- `FHE.div(x, y)` / `FHE.rem(x, y)` with an encrypted `y` - compile error.
  Only `(euint*, uintN)` overload exists; runtime `FHE.div(x, 0)` reverts
  with `DivisionByZero()`.
- Signed encrypted types `eint8`-`eint256` - declared but unusable;
  `@fhevm/solidity@0.11.1` ships zero `FHE.*` overloads.
- Hardcoding ACL/KMS/Coprocessor addresses or relayer URLs - inherit from
  `ZamaEthereumConfig`. Mainnet (chain 1) needs `MainnetConfig` on the
  frontend SDK side; never `SepoliaConfig` on chain 1.
- Mainnet API key in `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` / `VITE_*` - it ships to every
  visitor. Route through a backend proxy with `relayerRouteVersion: 1`.
- `userDecryptEbool(FhevmType, ...)` / `userDecryptEaddress(FhevmType, ...)`
  in Hardhat tests - only `userDecryptEuint` takes `FhevmType`.

## Hard limits (source-verified)

- `userDecrypt`: total ciphertext width <= 2048 bits per call (`check2048EncryptedBits`),
  <= 10 contract addresses (`MAX_USER_DECRYPT_CONTRACT_ADDRESSES`), <= 365-day
  EIP-712 grant (`MAX_USER_DECRYPT_DURATION_DAYS`).
- Per transaction: 20M HCU total, 5M sequential-depth HCU
  (`HCULimit.sol:50, 54`).
- Encrypted-input batch: <= 2048 bits, <= 256 variables.
- `FHE.randEuintX(upperBound)` - `upperBound` MUST be a power of 2.
- `userDecryptEuint*` returns `Promise<bigint>` - in tests compare with
  `1000n`, never `1000` (chai `.eq` does strict `===`).

## Encrypt + decrypt quick reference

Verified against `@zama-fhe/sdk@3.0.0`, `@zama-fhe/react-sdk@3.0.0`, `@fhevm/hardhat-plugin@0.4.2`, and the official guide https://docs.zama.org/protocol/sdk/guides/encrypt-decrypt.md.

```ts
/* Encrypt user input (browser, React; "use client" in Next.js) */
import { useEncrypt } from "@zama-fhe/react-sdk";
const { mutateAsync: encrypt } = useEncrypt();
const { handles, inputProof } = await encrypt({
  values: [{ value: 1000n, type: "euint64" }],
  contractAddress, userAddress,
});

/* Encrypt user input (Hardhat test) */
import { fhevm } from "hardhat";
const inp = fhevm.createEncryptedInput(contract.address, signer.address);
inp.add64(1000n);
const enc = await inp.encrypt();   /* enc.handles[0], enc.inputProof */

/* Decrypt confidential token balance (one EIP-712 prompt, then silent) */
const balance = await token.balanceOf();              /* returns bigint, NOT a wrapper */
const handle  = await token.confidentialBalanceOf();  /* raw bytes32 handle (Hex) */
import { useConfidentialBalance, useConfidentialBalances } from "@zama-fhe/react-sdk";
const { data } = useConfidentialBalance({ tokenAddress: cUSDT }, { refetchInterval: 5000 });

/* Decrypt arbitrary handles from a custom (non-token) contract */
await sdk.allow([contract.address]);
const values = await sdk.userDecrypt([{ handle, contractAddress: contract.address }]);
const cleartext = values[handle];                     /* bare Record - NOT .clearValues */
import { useAllow, useIsAllowed, useUserDecrypt } from "@zama-fhe/react-sdk";

/* Local development: cleartext mode (NOT allowed on chain 1 / 11155111) */
import { RelayerCleartext, hardhatCleartextConfig, hoodiCleartextConfig } from "@zama-fhe/sdk/cleartext";
const relayer = new RelayerCleartext(hardhatCleartextConfig);

/* Delegated decryption (decrypt someone else's balance) */
await token.delegateDecryption({ delegateAddress, expirationDate: Math.floor(Date.now()/1000) + 3600 });
/* Wait 1-2 minutes for gateway propagation, else DelegationNotPropagatedError */
const otherBal = await token.decryptBalanceAs(otherAddress, delegateAddress);
```

Pitfalls: `userDecrypt` returns bare `Record`, `publicDecrypt` returns `{ clearValues }`. `NoCiphertextError` = "never shielded" (show empty state, NOT "0"). COOP `same-origin` + COEP `require-corp`. Vite: `optimizeDeps.exclude: ["@zama-fhe/relayer-sdk"]` + `worker.format: "es"`. Mainnet: backend proxy with `x-api-key`, never `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` / `VITE_*`. `keypairTTL` default 30d, max 365d, `0` rejected at `ZamaSDK` construction.

## Public decryption is a 3-step flow

1. On-chain: `FHE.makePubliclyDecryptable(handle)`.
2. Off-chain: `await instance.publicDecrypt([handle])`, read
   `results.clearValues[handle]`.
3. On-chain: `FHE.checkSignatures(cts, abi.encode(clearValue), proof)` where
   `cts` order matches the off-chain `publicDecrypt` argument order. Swapping reverts with `KMSInvalidSigner(address)`.

## Browser

The SDK uses WASM with `SharedArrayBuffer`. Serve with
`Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin` and
`Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp`. With Vite, exclude the SDK
from `optimizeDeps` and set `worker.format: "es"` or WASM fails to load.

Next.js / Remix: relayer SDK + Wagmi persistent storage both need
`indexedDB`, which does not exist during SSR. Mark the file
`"use client"` and gate `initSDK` / `createInstance` behind `useEffect`.

