contract toolchain (`@fhevm/mock-utils@0.4.2`,
`@fhevm/hardhat-plugin@0.4.2`) peer-pins `@zama-fhe/relayer-sdk@0.4.1`
exact, while `@zama-fhe/sdk@3.0.0` declares `~0.4.2`. Installing both
yields a peer warning; if the lockfile hoists `0.4.2` the toolchain
runtime-aborts - pin `@zama-fhe/relayer-sdk: 0.4.1` in `package.json`
`overrides` to force `0.4.1` to win. New SDK requires `node >= 22`.
